      "judge_reason": "subprocess.run with shell=True on a dynamically constructed command string creates a command injection vector. The regex validation limits characters but shell=True still allows shell metacharacters like backticks or $() if they are not blocked by the regex. The regex only allows alphanumeric, dash, underscore, so injection is theoretically blocked, but shell=True is an unnecessary risk and violates defense-in-depth. Bandit correctly flags this as a security issue."
